tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE quantum_algorithm_metrics (
    algorithm_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    algorithm_name VARCHAR(255),
    algorithm_description TEXT,
    execution_time FLOAT,
    success_rate FLOAT,
    quantum_volume INT
);

CREATE TABLE QuantumAlgorithms (
    algorithm_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    algorithm_name VARCHAR(255),
    execution_time FLOAT,
    success_rate FLOAT,
    iterations INT
);

CREATE TABLE MachineLearningModels (
    model_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    model_name VARCHAR(255),
    model_type VARCHAR(50),
    input_features INT,
    output_classes INT
);

CREATE TABLE AlgorithmMetrics (
    metric_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    algorithm_id UUID REFERENCES QuantumAlgorithms(algorithm_id),
    model_id UUID REFERENCES MachineLearningModels(model_id),
    accuracy FLOAT,
    precision FLOAT,
    recall FLOAT
);

CREATE TABLE BenchmarkingResults (
    result_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    metric_id UUID REFERENCES AlgorithmMetrics(metric_id),
    execution_date DATE,
    execution_time FLOAT,
    success BOOLEAN
);

CREATE TABLE QuantumMetrics(
    metric_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    algorithm_id UUID NOT NULL,
    metric_name TEXT NOT NULL,
    metric_value FLOAT NOT NULL,
    measurement_time TIMESTAMP
);

CREATE TABLE QuantumModels(
    model_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    model_name TEXT NOT NULL,
    algorithm_id UUID NOT NULL,
    model_type TEXT NOT NULL,
    training_data_size INT NOT NULL
);

CREATE TABLE QuantumBenchmarks(
    benchmark_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    model_id UUID NOT NULL,
    benchmark_name TEXT NOT NULL,
    benchmark_result FLOAT NOT NULL,
    benchmark_time TIMESTAMP
);

CREATE TABLE QuantumAnalysis(
    analysis_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    model_id UUID NOT NULL,
    analysis_type TEXT NOT NULL,
    analysis_result TEXT NOT NULL,
    analysis_time TIMESTAMP
);
